nor [[Scott Walker (politician)|Scott Walker]] in the Eau Claire Circuit.\n\n{| class=\"wikitable\"\n! rowspan=\"2\" |Circuit\n! rowspan=\"2\" |Branch\n! rowspan=\"2\" |Incumbent\n! colspan=\"3\" |Elected\n! colspan=\"3\" |Defeated\n! Defeated in Primary\n|-\n!Name\n!Votes\n!%\n!Name\n!Votes\n!%\n!Name(s)\n|-\n! colspan=\"2\" | Ashland\n| Robert E. Eaton \n| '''Kelly J. McKnight'''\n| align=\"right\"| 2,181 \n| align=\"right\"| 97.72%\n| colspan=\"4\" align=\"center\" | \n|-\n! rowspan=\"2\" | Brown\n| 2\n| Thomas J. Walsh\n| '''Thomas J. Walsh'''\n| align=\"right\"| 28,323\n| align=\"right\"| 99.24%\n| colspan=\"4\" align=\"center\" | \n|-\n| 6\n| John P. Zakowski\n| '''John P. Zakowski'''\n| align=\"right\"| 30,141\n| align=\"right\"| 99.26%\n| colspan=\"4\" align=\"center\" | \n|-\n! colspan=\"2\" | Buffalo&ndash;Pepin\n|  James J. Duvall \n| '''Thomas W. Clark'''\n| align=\"right\"| 2,650\n| align=\"right\"| 56.58%\n| Roger M. Hillestad \n| align=\"right\"| 2,030\n| align=\"right\"| 43.34%\n| \n|-\n! colspan=\"2\" | Calumet\n| Jeffrey S. Froehlich\n| '''Jeffrey S. Froehlich'''\n| align=\"right\"| 5,531\n| align=\"right\"| 99.41%\n| colspan=\"4\" align=\"center\" | \n|-\n! Chippewa\n| 1\n| Steven H. Gibbs\n| '''Steven H. Gibbs'''\n| align=\"right\"| 8,170\n| align=\"right\"| 100.00%\n| colspan=\"4\" align=\"center\" | \n|-\n! colspan=\"2\" | Clark\n| Jon M. Counsell \n| '''Lyndsey Boon Brunette'''\n| align=\"right\"| 4,028\n| align=\"right\"| 76.40%\n| Roberta A. Heckes\n| align=\"right\"| 1,240\n| align=\"right\"| 23.52%\n|\n|-\n! Columbia\n| 3\n| Alan White \n| '''Troy D. Cross'''\n| align=\"right\"| 5,059\n| align=\"right\"| 50.27%\n| Brenda L. Yaskal\n| align=\"right\"| 4,974\n| align=\"right\"| 49.42%\n| Steven J. Sarbacker <br />Clifford C . Burdon\n|-\n! rowspan=\"3\" | Dane\n| 1\n| Timothy Samuelson\n| '''Susan M. Crawford'''\n| align=\"right\"| 59,048\n| align=\"right\"| 51.40%\n| Marilyn Townsend\n| align=\"right\"| 55,234\n| align=\"right\"| 49.08%\n| 